# Conventional commit: e.g.:
feat(x): adds feature to x.
fix(database): capture and handle connection failures.
style: reformats to std. form.
doc: updates README with build instructions.
#
# <type>[optional scope]: <description-in-present-tense>
#
# * types: fix, feat, build, chore, ci, docs, style, perf, test.
# * scope: affected module or component (optional)
# * use "!" for breaking changes, and add a footer describing the break.
#
# e.g.
# feat(api)!: adds more options to sort method(s).
#
# [optional body] 
#
# [optional footer(s)]
#
# BREAKING CHANGE: (e.g.) Uses unstable but faster sort.
#
